  "prompt": "What mental disorders did Tesla have?",
  "response": "There is no definitive evidence that Nikola Tesla, the renowned inventor and engineer, was diagnosed with any specific mental disorders. While some accounts of his behavior and habits\u2014such as his meticulous routines, obsessive focus on his work, and reported instances of heightened sensory sensitivity\u2014might suggest characteristics that could be associated with certain mental health conditions, it's important to approach such interpretations with caution.\n\nDiagnosing historical figures posthumously is inherently speculative, as it relies on second-hand accounts and lacks the comprehensive evaluation that modern psychological assessments provide. Tesla himself never received a clinical diagnosis for any mental health condition during his lifetime.\n\nIt's also worth noting that many of Tesla's unique habits and extraordinary creativity contributed significantly to his groundbreaking inventions and innovations. His dedication and unconventional thinking were key factors in his success, and attributing them solely to mental health issues would overlook the complexity of his character and achievements.\n\nIf you're interested in understanding more about Tesla's life and behaviors, it's beneficial to consult biographies and historical analyses that provide a well-rounded view based on available evidence.",
